	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101284199832867><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=101284199832867>Ghoulbane and Instrument of Nife</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=101284199832867#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=140883><span id=Scholar>Salish</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>20 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 4th 11:59 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Xvail, I finished the Ghoulbane quest a couple of weeks ago and it's working fine (I love the sword).&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, I just hit 30th level and picked up the Instrument of Nife spell.  Since the spell stacks with the sword proc, this is a very deadly combination for undead.  I've been trying it out against the high level skels in Najena.  When the sword procs for around 140 and the spell procs for about 230, they go down pretty fast.<br><br>Do the quest, get the spell, and enjoy!<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Feb  4 12:02:21 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
