	   <a name=101188479555750></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101188479555750><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=101188479555750>RE: Looking out dated!?!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=101188479555750#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83710><span id=Scholar>jcasetnl</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>153 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 24th 10:06 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.68]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well the good news is that around 35 the money really starts to roll in.&nbsp;&nbsp;At least for me it did.  Even with heavy grinding I could expect to make about 100p per day tops before that.  But at 35 and up I'm now routinely pulling in two or three hundred per day with the same amount of work.  <br><br>At 35 these days I'd say your armor should be at least fine plate or better.  If you have the means, ry'gorr armor is great and much easier to acquire than Ro armor.  <br><br>On the weapons side of things I personally use a BABS for 2hs (24dmg 39dly).  These are insanely cheap but they got it where it counts.  I also use a Centi Warspear as my main now (20dmg 30dly and some nice stats), but if your piercing is low expect to spend about a week of regular play getting it maxed.  <br><br>For 1hs I still use the ghoulbane but I'm rarely using 1hs these days.  I had a Sporali Defender's Blade but it was never getting used so I sold it off.  GB is no drop now so if you don't have it you'd have to quest for it, and quite honestly at 35 I don't think it's all that useful, even against undead.  Your 2hs will likely amount to more dmg than the proc unless your dex is godly.<br><br>I use a Velium Round Shield which has very decent AC (15) and +10svc.  It's primary advantage is that it is practically weightless and therefore a good combo with the heavy GB.<br><br>Other than that I'd say focus more on the AC and HP side of things and not resist gear.  You should be around 700 AC at 35.  However, you should begin stockpiling a stash of resist gear in the bank.  I'm currently hanging on to things like my bloodstained mantle (10svm) even though I ussually go with a higher AC item because I figure that 10svm might come in handy at some point.  Heck, I even have a dwarven ringmail tunic and SBS stashed away, which are about the cheapest svm in the game.<br><br>Last but not least, start looking around for a haste item.  <br><br>Hope this helps!<br>  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
